I have a reactor.conf like so:

```
reactor:
  - 'salt/job/*/ret/*':
    - /srv/salt/reactor/lcm_orchestrator_salt.sls
```

When a salt job throws an exception, it generates an event of the form:

```
2015-08-05 19:28:12,905 [salt.utils.event                         ][DEBUG   ][1051] Sending event - data = {'fun_args': ['raise'], 'jid': '20150805192812857271', 'return': 'The minion function caused an exception: Traceback (most recent call last):\n  File "/usr/lib/python2.6/site-packages/salt/minion.py", line 1161, in _thread_return\n   return_data = func(*args, **kwargs)\n  File "/var/cache/salt/minion/extmods/modules/lcm_test.py", line 37, in echo_raise\n    raise ValueError("Exception: " + str(data))\nValueError: Exception: raise\n', 'success': False, 'cmd': '_return', '_stamp': '2015-08-05T19:28:12.904754', 'fun': 'lcm_test.echo_raise', 'id': 'pod-minion-aus-jsf-admin', 'out': 'nested'}
```

Note that this event is generated by the salt infra, and that the 'return' contains a Traceback and one or more ':'.
This causes a new exception when the reactor is invoked - I assume because of the embedded ':' in the event

```
2015-08-05 19:28:12,913 [salt.utils.reactor                                 ][ERROR   ][1039] Failed to render "/
srv/salt/reactor/lcm_orchestrator_salt.sls":
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "/usr/lib/python2.6/site-packages/salt/utils/reactor.py", line 53, in render_reaction
    data=data)
